# Force LF line endings for source files and test fixtures so cross-platform
# Git checkouts (in particular Windows with core.autocrlf=true) produce
# byte-identical files. This is required by:
#  - rustfmt.toml `newline_style = "Unix"` (otherwise `cargo fmt --check`
#    fails on every .rs file on Windows runners).
#  - ridge-fmt golden fixture tests (`crates/ridge-fmt/tests/fixtures/*.ridge`)
#    whose `_expected.ridge` files encode the canonical LF output.

*.rs   text eol=lf
*.ridge   text eol=lf
*.toml text eol=lf
*.sh   text eol=lf

# Exception: this fixture deliberately holds CRLF line endings — it is the
# input that exercises ridge-fmt's CRLF→LF normalisation. Marking it as
# binary prevents Git from rewriting its line endings on checkout.
crates/ridge-fmt/tests/fixtures/10_crlf_input.ridge binary
